com.thinkaurelius.titan.core

Interface PropertyKey

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.apache.tinkerpop.gremlin.structure.Element, org.apache.tinkerpop.gremlin.structure.util.Host, Idfiable, Namifiable, RelationType, Removable, TitanElement, TitanSchemaElement, TitanSchemaType, TitanVertex, org.apache.tinkerpop.gremlin.structure.Vertex
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseKey, ImplicitKey, PropertyKeyVertex

    public interface PropertyKey
extends RelationType
    PropertyKey is an extension of RelationType for properties. Each property in Titan has a key.

    A property key defines the following characteristics of a property:

    • Data Type: The data type of the value for a given property of this key
    • Cardinality: The cardinality of the set of properties that may be associated with a single vertex through a particular key.
    Author:
    Matthias Bröcheler (me@matthiasb.com)
